<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-20811] Fix overlapping bootstraps; improve replay time and startup behaviours</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20811</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Bootstrap must first wait for a quorum to apply the sync point to ensure the DurableBefore Majority condition holds transitively,&lt;br/&gt;
        since later quorums may include the bootstrapping node which does not participate in the durability of preceding transactions&lt;br/&gt;
Also Improve:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Apply MaxDecidedRX filtering to CommandsForKey RX dependencies&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;optimise AbstractRanges.sliceMinimal (burn test hotspot)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Don&apos;t start shard schedulers on topology changes if not already started&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Only registerTransitive if waitingOnSync&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Reserve DurabilityRequest until ShardDurability is started&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Don&apos;t notify progress log if stopped&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Remove duplicate unmanaged filtering&lt;br/&gt;
Also fix:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Edge case in notification across bootstrap boundary by resubmitting Unmanaged to be recomputed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Serialization of CommandsForKey.TxnInfo.missing() collection when non-identity flag bits are present&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
